The paper deals with the detection and tracking of fast-moving objects in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for object detection, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the use of highlighting and temporal superresolution, which are related to computer graphics and visualization, and hence cs.GR (Graphics) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of tracking algorithms, which is a problem in robotics, and hence cs.RO (Robotics and Control) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of novel algorithms for object detection, which is a problem in artificial intelligence, and hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category.
